WEBVTT

00:03.369 --> 00:04.437
Voluntary?

00:04.470 --> 00:05.772
With good behavior
and time served,

00:05.806 --> 00:07.574
you could be out in seven.
It's a good deal.

00:07.608 --> 00:09.475
Not a chance.
Take the deal,
Eddie.

00:09.510 --> 00:11.778
We are not doing well
in there. They have pictures,

00:11.812 --> 00:13.714
they have the murder weapon,
and we have nothing.

00:13.747 --> 00:15.549
Two witnesses testified
that you told them

00:15.582 --> 00:16.449
you were going to kill
the victim.

00:16.482 --> 00:18.819
It was self-defense.
You said it in there.

00:18.852 --> 00:20.687
You stabbed him
seven times.

00:20.721 --> 00:22.055
Did you take a look
at that jury?

00:22.088 --> 00:23.590
Why the hell should I?

00:23.624 --> 00:25.458
Look at me.
With this deal,

00:25.491 --> 00:27.628
I can lobby for a lower
security facility,

00:27.661 --> 00:29.095
maybe even conjugal visits.

00:29.129 --> 00:31.197
In my opinion,
the D. A.'s offering you

00:31.231 --> 00:32.098
better than you deserve.

00:32.131 --> 00:34.334
Someone's got to get
that bony-assed bitch.

00:34.367 --> 00:36.102
Look, I've about
had it with you.

00:36.136 --> 00:39.105
Good. Then you can get
your not-so-bony-ass self

00:39.139 --> 00:40.140
Eddie.
Out of here.

00:40.173 --> 00:43.510
I ain't taking voluntary.
I paid you 90,000 bucks.

00:43.544 --> 00:44.645
Which is probably
drug money.

00:44.678 --> 00:47.080
You took it,
like you always have.

00:47.113 --> 00:50.483
Now why don't you take 20
of it and go buy a juror?

00:50.517 --> 00:54.154
I don't care.
Just get me off.

00:56.222 --> 00:59.259
( music playing )

01:44.638 --> 01:45.639
What's this I hear you offered

01:45.672 --> 01:47.307
that cokehead manslaughter?

01:47.340 --> 01:48.809
Relax, Richard.

01:48.842 --> 01:51.712
It was first degree, Helen.
Is this the Christmas spirit?

01:51.745 --> 01:53.446
He turned the deal down.

01:53.479 --> 01:54.314
Excuse me?

01:54.347 --> 01:56.416
The cokehead's sticking
to self-defense.

01:56.917 --> 02:00.286
What? That means
he'll have to testify.

02:00.787 --> 02:02.656
No problem. I testify.

02:02.689 --> 02:05.158
Yeah, there is a problem.
Once you take the stand,

02:05.191 --> 02:07.460
they could introduce all
your felonies to impeach you.

02:07.493 --> 02:10.496
Drug felonies. I never killed
anybody before, right, 'Genie?

02:10.531 --> 02:12.866
Well, I've never
killed anybody before either.

02:12.899 --> 02:15.836
You call me 'Genie one more
time, that could change.

02:15.869 --> 02:19.706
Look, just ask me the questions,
and I'll say what happened.

02:19.740 --> 02:21.341
Eddie, are you
coked up now?

02:21.374 --> 02:23.143
I'm in lock-up.
How do I get anything?

02:24.210 --> 02:25.946
Look, you've seen enough
of Helen Gamble to know

02:25.979 --> 02:27.313
she's going
to be aggressive.

02:27.347 --> 02:28.615
Let her come.

02:28.649 --> 02:30.851
Bobby, he's high. We can't
let him take the stand --

02:30.884 --> 02:33.787
Stay out of this, 'Genie.
You're second chair.

02:33.820 --> 02:34.955
Eugene, excuse us
for a second,

02:34.988 --> 02:36.256
would you, please?

02:42.462 --> 02:43.730
You want your 90 grand
back, Eddie?

02:43.764 --> 02:44.731
'Cause I'll write you
a check with interest

02:44.765 --> 02:45.832
right now and walk away.

02:47.000 --> 02:48.535
Business is good,
huh Bobby?

02:48.935 --> 02:51.772
You wouldn't walk away
from my money 10 years ago.

02:51.805 --> 02:56.543
What makes me sick here
is I helped build your firm.

02:56.577 --> 02:58.344
Over 10 years,
I poured a million bucks

02:58.378 --> 02:59.546
in and out of your place,
and you took it.

02:59.580 --> 03:01.247
You took it. You took it,

03:01.281 --> 03:03.249
knowing exactly
where it came from.

03:03.283 --> 03:04.951
Knowing exactly how
I got it. You took it.

03:04.985 --> 03:05.886
I'm not going
to listen to this.

03:05.919 --> 03:08.722
Hey, maybe you didn't
break any laws, Bobby,

03:08.755 --> 03:10.757
but you and I both know
you laundered my money.

03:10.791 --> 03:11.758
I'd give you a big retainer,

03:11.792 --> 03:14.427
you'd give me half back
after the case was over.

03:14.460 --> 03:17.230
You laundered drug money.

03:17.263 --> 03:19.833
Now you judge me.

03:21.401 --> 03:24.337
You stride in here
in your fancy suit.

03:24.370 --> 03:27.340
You moved up,
and now you judge me?

03:27.373 --> 03:29.409
Don't you lump me
into what you are.

03:29.442 --> 03:31.745
I was never what you are.
I'll never be what you are.

03:31.778 --> 03:33.013
I was a lawyer
representing scum...
EDDIE: You defended me.
You fought

03:33.046 --> 03:33.847
for me because
the money was right.

03:33.880 --> 03:35.516
Which I'm obviously
still doing today!

03:35.549 --> 03:36.917
Now you think you're
something too good!

03:36.950 --> 03:38.885
You stabbed a person
seven times.

03:38.919 --> 03:41.555
Eddie, you're a murderer.
That's how I judge you!

03:41.588 --> 03:44.558
Hey, counselor,
it was self-defense.

03:44.591 --> 03:45.692
Step back, Eddie.

03:48.529 --> 03:50.496
Step back.

03:57.704 --> 03:59.840
I had sold him some heroin
three days before.

03:59.873 --> 04:00.941
The victim?

04:00.974 --> 04:02.943
Yes, and then
he shows up at my house,

04:02.976 --> 04:05.045
rambling about how
the stuff wasn't pure.

04:05.078 --> 04:06.647
I could tell
he was wired.

04:06.680 --> 04:07.681
On heroin?

04:07.714 --> 04:09.349
Or something.

04:09.382 --> 04:10.884
Anyway, he starts
going on

04:10.917 --> 04:13.453
about how he's going
to mess me up,

04:13.486 --> 04:15.989
and he came at me.
We get into a struggle,

04:16.022 --> 04:18.959
and suddenly he's got me
by the throat,

04:18.992 --> 04:20.793
and that's when
I reached for my knife.

04:20.827 --> 04:21.995
Where was the knife?

04:22.028 --> 04:24.998
In my pocket.
It was a switchblade.

04:25.031 --> 04:27.901
He had me by the throat.
I wasn't getting any air.

04:27.934 --> 04:31.004
I'm thinking,
"This is it. I'm dying."

04:32.706 --> 04:34.775
And then I got my knife out
and just started stabbing.

04:34.808 --> 04:37.878
How many times did you
stab him with the knife, Eddie?

04:37.911 --> 04:41.682
I didn't know at the time.
They tell me seven.

04:41.715 --> 04:42.849
I just kept stabbing
at the guy

04:42.883 --> 04:43.884
till he fell off
of me.

04:44.685 --> 04:47.688
Eddie, why didn't
you call the police?

04:47.721 --> 04:51.024
Because I'm a drug dealer,
Mr. Donnell. I sell heroin.

04:51.057 --> 04:53.727
I didn't figure the police
to be too sympathetic,

04:53.760 --> 04:56.730
but I acted in self-defense
that night.

04:56.763 --> 04:59.399
I'm no model citizen,
I admit,

04:59.432 --> 05:01.602
but I'm no murderer.

05:01.635 --> 05:04.805
Seven times you stabbed him
before he fell off you?

05:04.838 --> 05:06.106
That's right.

05:06.139 --> 05:07.941
Because he was
strangling you.

05:07.974 --> 05:09.375
Yes.

05:09.409 --> 05:10.577
How much do you weigh,
Mr. Wicks?

05:10.611 --> 05:12.045
Around 175.

05:12.078 --> 05:13.479
Do you know how much
the victim weighed?

05:13.514 --> 05:14.548
No.

05:14.581 --> 05:17.350
Would it surprise you to learn
he weighed 135 pounds,

05:17.383 --> 05:18.852
40 pounds less than you?

05:18.885 --> 05:21.955
When a guy has you by the neck,
size doesn't matter too much.

05:21.988 --> 05:23.724
Doctors find any bruising
around your neck?

05:23.757 --> 05:24.591
No.

05:24.625 --> 05:26.627
Did the victim
owe you money, Mr. Wicks?

05:26.660 --> 05:28.094
This wasn't about that.

05:28.128 --> 05:30.631
Did the victim
owe you money, sir?

05:30.664 --> 05:31.632
Yes.

05:31.665 --> 05:32.633
How much?

05:32.666 --> 05:34.034
Around $60,000.

05:34.067 --> 05:36.402
This debt was incurred
through past drug sales?

05:36.436 --> 05:37.170
Yes.

05:37.203 --> 05:38.872
You've been convicted
three times

05:38.905 --> 05:41.575
for selling
and possessing drugs?

05:41.608 --> 05:44.044
I'm a drug guy. I said it,
but I'm not a killer.

05:44.077 --> 05:45.912
Did you tell Mr. Olson
you'd kill him

05:45.946 --> 05:47.147
if he didn't satisfy
his debt?

05:47.180 --> 05:49.382
I had previously
threatened him, yes,

05:49.415 --> 05:51.752
but this incident here
was self-defense.

05:51.785 --> 05:55.455
You said the victim
just showed up at your house.

05:55.488 --> 05:57.558
Did you call him
shortly before he came?

05:57.591 --> 05:59.960
Yes, to discuss
his outstanding account.

05:59.993 --> 06:01.695
You didn't invite him over
so you could kill him?

06:01.728 --> 06:02.829
Objection.
Objection.

06:02.863 --> 06:04.130
Sustained.

06:04.164 --> 06:07.033
Ever stab anybody else
with a switchblade, Mr. Wicks?

06:07.067 --> 06:10.637
Drug trafficking is
a tough trade, Ms. Gamble.

06:10.671 --> 06:13.574
Sometimes I've had
to use my knife,

06:13.607 --> 06:16.677
but this instance here
was self-defense.

06:16.710 --> 06:17.644
That's a yes.

06:17.678 --> 06:20.681
You have used your knife
to stab people before.

06:21.848 --> 06:22.849
Yes.

06:27.754 --> 06:30.691
Mistrial? Because of
the expression on my face?

06:30.724 --> 06:33.560
You all but told the jury
not to believe him.
I did no such thing.

06:33.594 --> 06:35.061
You were so obviously
rejecting his testimony.

06:35.095 --> 06:35.996
Forget it.

06:36.029 --> 06:37.598
Your honor.

06:37.631 --> 06:39.866
First of all,
I was not shooting any looks.

06:39.900 --> 06:42.468
Second, I wouldn't be conveying
that kind of a look anyway

06:42.503 --> 06:45.438
because I don't necessarily
believe that your little

06:45.471 --> 06:49.042
scum-sucking, lying,
murdering client is guilty.

06:49.075 --> 06:51.044
He could've just been
temporarily insane

06:51.077 --> 06:52.445
and under the delusion

06:52.478 --> 06:53.814
that he was stabbing
his own mother.

06:53.847 --> 06:54.881
You think that's funny?

06:55.849 --> 06:57.751
Who do you think
you're kidding?

06:57.784 --> 06:59.052
You're in here
looking for a mistrial

06:59.085 --> 07:00.787
because you know
just like I know

07:00.821 --> 07:02.856
what the verdict
is going to be.

07:02.889 --> 07:03.824
Let me tell you,
counsel.

07:03.857 --> 07:06.693
I don't play those games.
And just for asking,

07:06.727 --> 07:08.595
I'm hitting you
with a $500 fine.

07:08.629 --> 07:09.696
Appealed.

07:09.730 --> 07:12.966
So noted. Mistrial.

07:18.104 --> 07:20.006
He actually moved
for a mistrial?

07:20.040 --> 07:21.742
You know Bobby.
If things are desperate,

07:21.775 --> 07:23.209
he'll try anything.

07:23.243 --> 07:24.878
I suppose if I ever
killed anybody,

07:24.911 --> 07:26.112
he'd be the guy I'd call.

07:27.280 --> 07:30.150
Helen, I, uh, I notice you got
a little mistletoe hanging.

07:30.183 --> 07:31.585
Where?

07:35.055 --> 07:37.558
Oh, God. Maintenance
must have done that.

07:37.591 --> 07:38.859
Even so...

07:38.892 --> 07:40.126
Don't harass me,
Richard.

07:40.160 --> 07:42.062
You liked my kiss.
You said so.

07:42.095 --> 07:43.063
I said it was nice.

07:43.096 --> 07:44.931
That doesn't mean
it couldn't use a little work.

07:45.632 --> 07:46.633
( sighs )

07:46.667 --> 07:48.535
Oh, now you're hurt.

07:48.569 --> 07:50.504
What was wrong with it?

07:50.537 --> 07:51.538
It was lovely.

07:51.572 --> 07:53.640
No, no,
don't patronize me, Helen.

07:53.674 --> 07:55.576
Just tell me.

07:55.609 --> 07:58.011
( sighs )
Okay, well,

07:58.044 --> 08:00.747
your little tongue
was shooting around everywhere

08:00.781 --> 08:03.049
like a lizard
trying to catch a fly.

08:03.083 --> 08:04.651
That's a technique.

08:04.685 --> 08:07.588
Technique? Richard,
it was darting in and out.

08:07.621 --> 08:09.523
All right, look.

08:16.096 --> 08:17.898
That's what
a good kiss is like.

08:17.931 --> 08:20.000
The tongue should know
what it's doing.

08:26.773 --> 08:29.109
He got to you,
didn't he?

08:29.142 --> 08:31.177
Well, he had a point.

08:31.211 --> 08:34.715
I half-built this place
doing drug cases.

08:34.748 --> 08:37.784
Should I give you the speech
you always give me?

08:37.818 --> 08:39.184
Drug cases
subsidize --

08:39.219 --> 08:41.587
No, I don't need
the speech.

08:41.621 --> 08:43.890
It went a little
beyond that with Eddie.

08:43.924 --> 08:46.192
What do you mean?

08:46.226 --> 08:49.630
Well, we were friends.

08:49.663 --> 08:50.797
You know,
I'd hang out with him

08:50.831 --> 08:52.566
after the case was over.

08:52.599 --> 08:54.701
I'd suppress the evidence,
he'd throw a little party,

08:54.735 --> 08:56.703
and I'd celebrate with him.

08:56.737 --> 08:57.638
You know,
he was the client

08:57.671 --> 09:00.040
and a good businessman
caters to the client.

09:00.073 --> 09:02.008
I think I always
led him to believe

09:03.009 --> 09:04.110
that I really liked him.

09:04.911 --> 09:05.879
Did you?

09:05.912 --> 09:07.280
Maybe I did.

09:08.314 --> 09:10.784
I think when someone's
buttering your bread,

09:10.817 --> 09:11.618
you want to like him.

09:14.988 --> 09:16.723
Did he launder money
through this place?

09:20.293 --> 09:21.327
Probably.

09:22.963 --> 09:25.031
It was never said,
but, you know,

09:25.065 --> 09:27.233
he'd give me
a $25,000 cash retainer

09:27.267 --> 09:28.001
for a 2-day trial,

09:28.034 --> 09:30.937
and I'd pay him back
the unused.

09:30.971 --> 09:34.841
Yeah, it was probably
the equivalent of laundering.

09:38.945 --> 09:41.982
I guess I was dirty, too,
Lindsay,

09:42.015 --> 09:43.283
and that's why
he can't bear

09:43.316 --> 09:45.786
me passing judgment
on him today.

09:45.819 --> 09:48.388
Bobby, you were
in a legitimate business.

09:48.421 --> 09:50.624
He wasn't. He sees all
that you've accomplished

09:50.657 --> 09:51.992
and how he stayed
in the same place,

09:52.025 --> 09:52.959
and he's angry.

09:52.993 --> 09:56.196
No, he's angry because
when I needed his money,

09:56.229 --> 09:57.598
I liked him.

09:58.732 --> 10:01.101
And now that I don't,

10:02.402 --> 10:03.604
I don't.

10:05.205 --> 10:06.272
Well...

10:07.708 --> 10:09.743
it's all about over,
anyway.

10:09.776 --> 10:10.844
He'll get murder two
at best.

10:10.877 --> 10:13.146
He's looking
at a life sentence.

10:13.179 --> 10:15.115
Consider him
lost business.

10:15.148 --> 10:17.951
I haven't lost yet.

10:28.394 --> 10:30.363
Are you saying
we got no shot?

10:30.396 --> 10:32.365
I'm saying
it's a long shot.

10:32.398 --> 10:34.234
We can argue the elements,
but in my opinion,

10:34.267 --> 10:35.836
the jury has already
made up its mind.

10:35.869 --> 10:36.970
I paid you enough money --

10:37.003 --> 10:40.040
Will you stop with the money?
You can't buy acquittals.

10:40.073 --> 10:41.074
How about you, 'Genie?

10:41.107 --> 10:43.009
Would you like me
to take your head off?

10:44.010 --> 10:45.445
What, you think if
a lawyer attacks his client,

10:45.478 --> 10:47.280
it buys him a mistrial
or something?

10:47.313 --> 10:48.248
Would it?

10:48.281 --> 10:50.183
Look Eddie, manslaughter is
our best bet --

10:50.216 --> 10:51.217
I ain't taking
manslaughter!

10:51.251 --> 10:52.352
You want murder two
or murder one?

10:52.385 --> 10:53.119
'cause that's what
you're going to get.

10:53.153 --> 10:55.722
You want a piece
of me, Eddie, huh?

10:55.756 --> 10:56.456
You haven't
got your knife now,

10:56.489 --> 10:57.658
and I weigh
more than a buck 40.

10:57.691 --> 11:00.193
I wouldn't need my knife.
I could pay you to play dead.

11:00.226 --> 11:02.328
All right.

11:05.198 --> 11:08.401
Go in there
and argue the elements.

11:10.103 --> 11:12.138
Just argue the elements.

11:22.248 --> 11:23.950
It's absolutely impossible.

11:23.984 --> 11:25.151
Are you sure, doctor?

11:25.185 --> 11:27.087
For the victim
to continue strangling

11:27.120 --> 11:28.321
with seven stab wounds?

11:28.354 --> 11:30.490
The loss of blood alone
would have dropped him,

11:30.524 --> 11:32.492
plus the knife
hit major arteries

11:32.526 --> 11:35.095
in both the heart
and neck.

11:35.128 --> 11:37.097
This was not
self-defense.

11:37.130 --> 11:38.464
Objection.

11:38.498 --> 11:41.467
Sustained. Just give us
the medicals, doctor.

11:41.502 --> 11:44.771
Dr. Foster, were you able
to make a determination

11:44.805 --> 11:46.272
as to the order
of the wounds?

11:46.306 --> 11:49.175
Well, first,
the wounds on the hands

11:49.209 --> 11:50.443
looked to be
defensive in nature,

11:50.476 --> 11:52.278
as if he had
his palms up to block.

11:52.312 --> 11:54.180
The idea that his hands
were on the defendant's neck

11:54.214 --> 11:56.216
at the time
he received them --

11:56.249 --> 11:58.218
also impossible.

11:58.251 --> 11:59.786
Is he testifying
to the order here?

11:59.820 --> 12:00.987
I'm about to, counsel.

12:01.021 --> 12:03.256
Then please do so, doctor.

12:03.289 --> 12:06.259
The hands came first,

12:06.292 --> 12:08.762
the jugular vein in the neck
was then severed,

12:08.795 --> 12:11.164
and while the victim
was clutching his neck,

12:11.197 --> 12:14.334
he was then stabbed
in the arm, then the heart.

12:14.367 --> 12:17.237
The wound to the atrium
in the heart was the fatal one.

12:17.270 --> 12:20.440
Now, it's your medical opinion
that the victim's hands

12:20.473 --> 12:22.442
were not
on the defendant's neck

12:22.475 --> 12:25.812
at the time he received
the fatal wound to the heart?

12:25.846 --> 12:27.981
That is
my medical opinion, yes.

12:30.884 --> 12:32.853
Aah! ( gasping )

12:32.886 --> 12:33.920
Stop that man!

12:33.954 --> 12:36.122
BOBBY: Eddie, no!

12:36.156 --> 12:37.558
Eddie!
JUDGE SWACKHEIM: Bailiff!

12:37.591 --> 12:39.492
Stop that man!

12:39.526 --> 12:41.127
Hey, hey!

12:41.161 --> 12:42.395
Security, come in here!

12:42.428 --> 12:44.831
Get that man
out of my court!

12:44.865 --> 12:47.300
( screaming )

12:47.333 --> 12:48.802
Cuff him!

12:50.504 --> 12:51.471
You okay?

12:51.505 --> 12:53.507
Yeah, and you? Helen?

12:53.540 --> 12:55.576
Helen?

12:55.609 --> 12:57.110
She's still breathing.
Get an ambulance!

12:57.143 --> 12:58.945
( Eddie groaning )

12:58.979 --> 13:00.413
Get an ambulance!

13:02.248 --> 13:04.250
Just lie still,
Helen.
I'm okay.

13:04.284 --> 13:06.252
Lie still.
I can get up.

13:06.286 --> 13:07.554
Stay back, sir.
Let me through.

13:07.588 --> 13:08.454
She's my girlfriend.
Let me through.

13:08.488 --> 13:12.025
I'm not your girlfriend.
One date, Richard.

13:12.058 --> 13:13.994
Helen.
Bobby, I'm okay!

13:14.027 --> 13:15.261
You're going to the hospital
to get checked out.

13:15.295 --> 13:17.297
I'm not his girlfriend.

13:20.133 --> 13:21.101
Is she okay?

13:21.134 --> 13:22.102
From what I gather.

13:22.135 --> 13:23.103
What hospital?

13:23.136 --> 13:24.437
Mass general.
I'm going.

13:24.470 --> 13:25.506
Wait. She's being
released already.

13:25.539 --> 13:26.306
