I was just sacrificed
up there.

25:02.569 --> 25:03.937
It has nothing to do
with this case.

25:03.970 --> 25:05.906
I'm a good M.E.
This is disgusting.

25:05.939 --> 25:08.174
It's disgusting. Why would
anybody ever testify

25:08.208 --> 25:09.910
if they can --
This is disgusting!

25:09.943 --> 25:11.545
Unfortunately,
personal lives

25:11.578 --> 25:13.680
are becoming
more and more fair game.

25:13.714 --> 25:15.949
Then why would any witness
in his right mind

25:15.982 --> 25:17.718
ever come forward
or do my job?

25:17.751 --> 25:19.285
Well, if he chooses
to do your job,

25:19.319 --> 25:20.186
he should certainly
think twice

25:20.220 --> 25:22.222
about taming his shrew
with a corpse handy.

25:22.255 --> 25:23.824
Oh, you think
that's funny?

25:23.857 --> 25:26.560
It's not funny, but we might
need to explain.

25:26.593 --> 25:27.961
It happened in the privacy
of my office.

25:27.994 --> 25:29.796
Again, having
a cadaver nearby --

25:29.830 --> 25:31.231
Shut up!

25:31.264 --> 25:33.133
I say we don't rehabilitate.
There's no point.

25:33.166 --> 25:34.300
Let's go to closings.

25:34.334 --> 25:37.003
I don't think they really
shook you on anything relevant.

25:37.037 --> 25:38.839
Oh, you don't think they shook
me, Ms. Gamble? I resign.

25:38.872 --> 25:41.975
I don't ever want to be
a player in this system.
You can't resign now.

25:42.008 --> 25:43.577
You can't resign now.

25:43.610 --> 25:44.945
At least wait
till after the trial.

25:44.978 --> 25:47.247
I was raped in there.
I was humiliated.

25:47.280 --> 25:50.851
I was -- Hail, hail
to our great justice system.

25:50.884 --> 25:53.153
Oh, great.

25:54.320 --> 25:57.123
Well, we better work
on the closing.

26:12.272 --> 26:15.075
JUDGE SWACKHEIM:
Miss Gamble.

26:15.108 --> 26:18.979
You know, ever since
the O. J. Simpson trial,

26:19.012 --> 26:21.381
I've had a hard time
defending this process

26:21.414 --> 26:23.817
to non-lawyers.

26:23.850 --> 26:26.252
The way I try
to explain it is that

26:26.286 --> 26:29.055
that was just
an aberrant runaway proceeding

26:29.089 --> 26:32.392
with renegade,
unscrupulous lawyers,

26:32.425 --> 26:35.962
a judge who couldn't
control his room,

26:35.996 --> 26:37.397
combined with total

26:37.430 --> 26:40.400
and utter disregard
for integrity.

26:40.433 --> 26:42.736
And I promised
my friends that

26:42.769 --> 26:45.271
that is just not
the way it is.

26:45.305 --> 26:49.242
But every once in a while
you get a case

26:49.275 --> 26:52.713
that is every bit as disgusting
as the televised debacle

26:52.746 --> 26:54.981
would have the public believe.

26:55.015 --> 26:58.118
We certainly witnessed it
here, didn't we?

26:58.151 --> 27:00.086
The defendant
physically attacked me,

27:00.120 --> 27:02.088
the judge
went off his medication,

27:02.122 --> 27:05.726
and the defense lawyers
were blatantly despicable.

27:05.759 --> 27:06.760
Objection.
Objection.

27:06.793 --> 27:07.894
Sustained.

27:07.928 --> 27:10.731
One thing
the judge did right, however,

27:10.764 --> 27:14.267
was to forcefully remind you
that this case

27:14.300 --> 27:16.903
is only about evidence.

27:16.937 --> 27:19.005
It has nothing to do

27:19.039 --> 27:22.843
with whether a medical examiner
sexually gratified himself,

27:22.876 --> 27:24.745
it has nothing to do

27:24.778 --> 27:27.180
with cases that took place
in Los Angeles,

27:27.213 --> 27:29.750
or whether somebody
cheated on his wife.

27:29.783 --> 27:32.285
The defense would love
to have you focus on that,

27:32.318 --> 27:34.855
but this case is about
who killed Philip Olson,

27:34.888 --> 27:36.957
and we know who did.

27:36.990 --> 27:41.194
The defendant admitted
he stabbed the man seven times.

27:41.227 --> 27:46.266
1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7.

27:46.299 --> 27:48.935
He stabbed the man seven times
with a knife.

27:48.969 --> 27:51.337
That is not in dispute,
ladies and gentlemen.

27:51.371 --> 27:53.473
It's uncontested,

27:53.507 --> 27:57.944
but since a conviction means
an automatic life sentence,

27:57.978 --> 28:01.414
defendants often
roll the dice,

28:01.447 --> 28:04.818
and why shouldn't they?
What do they have to lose?

28:04.851 --> 28:06.186
Might as well
make something up.

28:06.219 --> 28:08.021
There's no reward
for telling the truth.

28:08.054 --> 28:10.123
The life sentence
is automatic.

28:11.792 --> 28:16.229
In this case, the fabrication
is self-defense.

28:17.764 --> 28:19.800
Self-defense.

28:21.768 --> 28:23.269
He stabbed the man
seven times,

28:23.303 --> 28:25.071
including once
in the heart

28:25.105 --> 28:27.908
and once in the throat.

28:27.941 --> 28:29.943
Self-defense.

28:29.976 --> 28:32.045
No bruising
on the defendant's neck,

28:32.078 --> 28:36.482
which an attempted strangulation
most certainly would have left.

28:36.517 --> 28:38.919
He's threatened to kill
the victim before.

28:38.952 --> 28:42.989
He's a convicted drug dealer
who has stabbed people before,

28:43.023 --> 28:46.459
but, hey, self-defense.

28:46.492 --> 28:50.764
Even they know how ridiculous
that theory sounds.

28:50.797 --> 28:54.835
That's why Mr. Wicks decided
to go for a mistrial.

28:54.868 --> 28:57.838
Mug the D. A., have the lawyers
jumping up and down,

28:57.871 --> 29:00.541
turn the whole proceeding
into a giant circus,

29:00.574 --> 29:04.210
and the judge might put a stop
to the whole thing.

29:04.244 --> 29:06.547
At a minimum,
he guarantees himself

29:06.580 --> 29:10.116
a new trial on appeal.

29:10.150 --> 29:15.388
And, hey, if he happens
to be so lucky

29:15.421 --> 29:20.026
as to get
that one gullible juror,

29:20.060 --> 29:22.863
who knows?

29:22.896 --> 29:25.832
And that's
today's judicial system,

29:25.866 --> 29:27.834
ladies and gentlemen.

29:27.868 --> 29:30.236
Words like "justice"
and "honor" and "respect" --

29:30.270 --> 29:31.838
they don't apply.

29:31.872 --> 29:32.806
Lawyers don't get hired today

29:32.839 --> 29:35.008
because they're dignified
or well thought of.

29:35.041 --> 29:39.145
It's winning and losing,
like every business.

29:39.179 --> 29:42.583
It comes down
to winning and losing,

29:42.616 --> 29:46.219
and I'm ashamed
to be a part of it.

29:46.252 --> 29:48.989
I'm embarrassed
to be a practitioner

29:49.022 --> 29:51.291
of what trial law
has become,

29:51.324 --> 29:53.594
which is a joke.

29:53.627 --> 29:57.564
Criminal trials
are a joke.

29:57.598 --> 30:00.166
Maybe one day
I'll go on to teach,

30:00.200 --> 30:02.168
and I'll say that.

30:02.202 --> 30:04.204
Some student
will raise his hand

30:04.237 --> 30:06.607
and ask me
to give an example.

30:06.640 --> 30:08.341
I'll say, "Sure.

30:08.374 --> 30:11.344
"Once I had a case
where the defendant

30:11.377 --> 30:15.348
"stabbed an unarmed man
seven times,

30:15.381 --> 30:20.086
"then walked into court
claiming self-defense.

30:20.120 --> 30:22.222
It's all a joke."

30:34.234 --> 30:37.237
It's a joke we've gone
this far, isn't it?

30:37.270 --> 30:40.106
Like Ms. Gamble says,

30:40.140 --> 30:42.242
seven times he stabbed him.

30:42.275 --> 30:43.644
That tells the story.

30:43.677 --> 30:46.212
It's a joke we've wasted
all your time,

30:46.246 --> 30:49.315
the judge's time,

30:49.349 --> 30:50.651
over $100,000
of the taxpayers' money.

30:50.684 --> 30:53.920
That's a joke.
On the easy ones,

30:53.954 --> 30:56.890
we should be able to skip
the carnival of a trial

30:56.923 --> 30:58.358
and just send the guy
to prison.

30:58.391 --> 31:01.294
He stabbed him seven times.

31:01.327 --> 31:03.530
How simple can it be?

31:03.564 --> 31:05.131
That's why
the medical examiner

31:05.165 --> 31:07.133
didn't even go to the scene.

31:07.167 --> 31:08.569
That's why
he didn't spend much time

31:08.602 --> 31:10.937
examining the victim's hands.

31:10.971 --> 31:12.673
How much more simple
can a case get?

31:12.706 --> 31:16.242
Why the hell are we
even bothering with a trial?

31:16.276 --> 31:19.680
Drug-dealing scum --
Why even bother?

31:19.713 --> 31:22.248
Hey, look at me.
Am I disturbing you?

31:22.282 --> 31:24.084
You got a problem
listening to this?

31:24.117 --> 31:26.119
Tell the judge,
and he'll let you off.

31:26.152 --> 31:27.654
Mr. Donnell,
do not address the jurors.

31:27.688 --> 31:31.257
Don't address the jurors?
This is my closing argument.

31:31.291 --> 31:32.993
Who should I be talking to,
the wall?

31:33.026 --> 31:33.994
You know what I mean.

31:34.027 --> 31:35.161
Maybe I should talk
to the wall.

31:35.195 --> 31:37.598
Drug-dealing,
stabbing client --

31:37.631 --> 31:39.399
maybe I'll have a better chance
of moving the wall.

31:39.432 --> 31:42.669
This case is like pounding up
against a wall!

31:42.703 --> 31:43.937
Mr. Donnell!

31:43.970 --> 31:44.605
The reason we bother

31:44.638 --> 31:45.606
to go through a trial

31:45.639 --> 31:48.642
is because sometimes
things aren't as they seem.

31:48.675 --> 31:51.144
Sometimes things
aren't so obvious.

31:51.177 --> 31:53.179
The victim tried
to strangle him.

31:53.213 --> 31:55.015
The prosecution doesn't
want to believe that,

31:55.048 --> 31:56.316
you may not want
to believe that,

31:56.349 --> 31:57.684
but you at least
have to ask yourself

31:57.718 --> 32:00.954
if Eddie Wicks planned
to kill Philip Olson,

32:00.987 --> 32:03.256
would he really invite him over
to his own house?

32:03.289 --> 32:07.227
Would it happen in such a messy,
unplanned way?

32:07.260 --> 32:09.730
The victim owed him
over $60,000,

32:09.763 --> 32:12.298
which he was working
on paying back.

32:12.332 --> 32:14.568
Now, most drug dealers
tend to like money

32:14.601 --> 32:16.202
more than murdering people.

32:16.236 --> 32:19.405
Why would he kill the guy
and say goodbye to the money?

32:19.439 --> 32:21.207
Did the prosecution
address that?

32:21.241 --> 32:25.045
Did they offer
any real motive here?

32:25.078 --> 32:26.312
No. They just
count stab wounds --

32:26.346 --> 32:28.749
1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7 --

32:28.782 --> 32:31.618
and hope you skip over
the motive part.

32:31.652 --> 32:34.287
Now, she talks
about winning and losing

32:34.320 --> 32:36.056
and how disgusting
it's become.

32:36.089 --> 32:37.090
You don't think
they've tried to win?

32:37.123 --> 32:39.392
They've put up
a medical examiner

32:39.425 --> 32:41.327
who listed off a series
of absolute

32:41.361 --> 32:44.097
impossibilities to things
that were possible.

32:44.130 --> 32:45.431
It was, in fact, possible

32:45.465 --> 32:47.768
for a man to get stabbed
in the neck

32:47.801 --> 32:49.770
and yet continue to strangle.

32:49.803 --> 32:52.072
That is possible.

32:52.105 --> 32:55.341
Dr. Foster testified that
it was impossible at first.

32:55.375 --> 32:57.778
Was he mistaken?
Did he lie,

32:57.811 --> 33:01.014
or did he just overstate it,
as he said?

33:01.047 --> 33:03.717
He's up here looking for a win,
ladies and gentlemen.

33:03.750 --> 33:05.351
You can count on that.

33:05.385 --> 33:07.521
One function
of the medical examiner's job

33:07.554 --> 33:09.322
is to be able to get on
this witness stand

33:09.355 --> 33:12.125
and be a persuasive
prosecutorial witness

33:12.158 --> 33:13.459
and help them
secure convictions,

33:13.493 --> 33:15.762
help them win,

33:15.796 --> 33:19.566
and that's what
he was doing.

33:19.600 --> 33:21.101
Now, the district attorney says

33:21.134 --> 33:25.338
she's ashamed to be
a part of it.

33:25.371 --> 33:28.408
Right now there are over 100
people sitting on death row

33:28.441 --> 33:30.544
for crimes they didn't commit,

33:30.577 --> 33:33.647
and if Eddie Wicks were
convicted in California,

33:33.680 --> 33:36.282
the state that fired Dr. Foster
for being too sloppy,

33:36.316 --> 33:37.818
he would also be on death row.

33:37.851 --> 33:39.820
And how many times
have we seen

33:39.853 --> 33:42.122
after the man sitting
on death row is cleared,

33:42.155 --> 33:45.291
after the guy sitting 30 years
in prison is cleared

33:45.325 --> 33:47.160
on newly discovered
DNA evidence,

33:47.193 --> 33:48.428
or after the wrong man
is executed,

33:48.461 --> 33:51.264
how many times have we seen
the D. A. Say,

33:51.297 --> 33:54.400
"I'm ashamed to be a part
of the process"?

33:54.434 --> 33:57.303
They just say mistakes happen.

33:57.337 --> 34:01.575
Well, that's right,
mistakes happen,

34:01.608 --> 34:04.845
and even when it seems
so obvious, mistakes happen,

34:04.878 --> 34:08.313
and nobody -- not her,
not him, not you --

34:08.348 --> 34:10.416
nobody can be sure
that a big mistake

34:10.449 --> 34:13.418
isn't happening right here
right now.

34:13.453 --> 34:15.856
It could have gone down
exactly the way

34:15.889 --> 34:17.489
my client said it did.

34:17.524 --> 34:19.324
The medical examiner knows it.

34:19.359 --> 34:21.862
You heard him admit on cross
under oath "possible" --

34:21.895 --> 34:24.429
possible it happened
just like Mr. Wicks said,

34:24.464 --> 34:27.668
possible the prosecution
is wrong.

34:27.701 --> 34:28.869
And I am not ashamed
to stand before you

34:28.902 --> 34:31.437
and say you cannot
send a man to prison

34:31.471 --> 34:33.106
for the rest of his life

34:33.139 --> 34:35.576
when there's a chance
the prosecution is wrong.

34:35.609 --> 34:39.145
This is why we have trials,
ladies and gentlemen.

34:39.179 --> 34:43.283
This is why we bother,

34:43.315 --> 34:46.351
and I am not ashamed
to be a part of it.

34:46.386 --> 34:48.454
I am proud
to be a defense attorney.

34:48.487 --> 34:50.724
I am proud to be the one
jumping up and down,

34:50.757 --> 34:53.659
even on cases where everything
seems so obvious.

34:53.694 --> 34:54.860
I am proud to be the one

34:54.895 --> 34:56.862
making the state
prove its burden

34:56.897 --> 34:58.665
beyond all reasonable doubt

34:58.699 --> 35:02.669
before taking
a man's life away forever,

35:02.703 --> 35:07.508
and I do not think
it's a joke.

35:07.541 --> 35:09.576
Now, you have two choices.

35:09.610 --> 35:11.411
You can go back there
and say,

35:11.444 --> 35:14.915
"drug-dealing scum --
let's lock him up anyway,"

35:14.948 --> 35:18.484
or you can admit
there was doubt,

35:18.519 --> 35:21.187
admit the state
put on nothing

35:21.221 --> 35:23.456
to contradict
Eddie Wicks' testimony

35:23.489 --> 35:25.659
and do the job
you were sworn to do

35:25.692 --> 35:29.930
when you signed on as jurors.

35:29.963 --> 35:33.499
But if you choose
to ignore that obligation,

35:33.534 --> 35:37.504
if you choose to say
forget reasonable doubt,

35:37.538 --> 35:40.507
forget the state's burden
of proof

35:40.541 --> 35:44.511
and convict him anyway...

35:44.545 --> 35:49.516
well, then Ms. Gamble's right,
after all.

35:49.550 --> 35:54.521
The system is, in fact...

35:54.555 --> 35:56.857
a joke.

36:16.510 --> 36:17.611
He was good.

36:17.644 --> 36:18.612
All he needed to do

36:18.645 --> 36:19.613
was persuade
one lone imbecile,

36:19.646 --> 36:21.247
and he's got --

36:21.281 --> 36:22.248
he's not going
to persuade.

36:22.282 --> 36:23.349
Helen,
you said it yourself --

36:23.383 --> 36:24.818
one idiot
beats a conviction.

36:24.851 --> 36:26.920
He just delivered
a damn good closing argument.

36:26.953 --> 36:28.555
So, maybe they'll beat
murder one.

36:28.589 --> 36:30.356
Even with murder two,
they've got an appeal.

36:30.390 --> 36:31.592
Ay, but Swackheim's right.

36:31.625 --> 36:33.426
With a murder two conviction
in the bank,

36:33.459 --> 36:35.261
they'll have to plead out
on manslaughter.

36:37.531 --> 36:38.464
You believe that?

36:38.498 --> 36:40.601
Guy stabs somebody
seven times,

36:40.634 --> 36:44.270
we're sitting here looking
at manslaughter as a victory.

36:53.313 --> 36:54.515
You phoned it in.

36:58.752 --> 37:01.622
Thanks.

37:01.655 --> 37:03.657
Something I said?

37:06.292 --> 37:10.030
It's not that I believe
in you, Eddie.

37:10.063 --> 37:13.634
It's more like...

37:13.667 --> 37:16.570
I need to believe in me.

37:17.804 --> 37:20.373
That and you're not
positive I'm guilty.

37:20.406 --> 37:24.244
And there's that.

37:29.916 --> 37:32.553
( door opens )

37:32.586 --> 37:35.421
Bobby,
the judge wants to see you.

37:42.629 --> 37:45.031
As soon as we get
our verdict,

37:45.065 --> 37:48.769
you will be proceeding
directly to jail,

37:48.802 --> 37:50.403
whether your client does
or not.

37:50.436 --> 37:51.572
Why?

37:51.605 --> 37:53.540
Because I'm holding you
in contempt.

37:53.574 --> 37:55.676
The only reason
I didn't do it earlier

37:55.709 --> 37:58.512
is because I didn't want
to prejudice the case,

37:58.545 --> 38:00.514
but the disrespect
you have shown me

38:00.547 --> 38:02.448
in this trial will not
go unpunished, counselor.

38:02.482 --> 38:04.084
Look, I know you're out
of your mind --

38:04.117 --> 38:06.419
Bobby.
Keep talking.

38:06.452 --> 38:07.253
You say you don't want
to prejudice the case --

38:07.287 --> 38:09.389
you call my client scum
in open court.

38:09.690 --> 38:11.391
The fact that you even let
this thing continue --

38:11.424 --> 38:12.793
any disrespect
I showed to you

38:12.826 --> 38:14.394
was well earned,
trust me.

38:14.427 --> 38:15.228
Listen, you little --

38:15.261 --> 38:16.396
You should at least
have the integrity

38:16.429 --> 38:18.799
To hold yourself
in contempt.

38:18.832 --> 38:20.500
You were a blight
on that room.

38:20.534 --> 38:21.968
You should have your robe
stripped away,

38:22.002 --> 38:23.436
and when this case is over,

38:23.469 --> 38:25.872
in addition to all
of my appeals on record,

38:25.906 --> 38:28.542
I will be bringing a motion
to have you removed

38:28.575 --> 38:30.110
because judges like you
are a cancer.
And I hope you win!

38:30.143 --> 38:31.812
Yes, I would rather
sit by a beach

38:31.845 --> 38:33.547
instead of listening
to lawyers like you...
You're a dead rot!

38:33.580 --> 38:34.981
And if this system has
any chance of ever working,

38:35.015 --> 38:37.050
with your gross,
vile clients
it has to weed itself

38:37.083 --> 38:38.519
who violate me...
of people who have
no business being judges,

38:38.552 --> 38:40.420
and you would be
at the top of the list!

38:40.453 --> 38:41.922
That the stench
it's become --
You are disgraceful!

38:41.955 --> 38:44.725
You are the stench!
You bring the stink!

38:44.758 --> 38:45.792
You are an arrogant redneck
son of a bitch!

38:45.826 --> 38:47.427
Well, you can bring it
right into the cell with you!

38:47.460 --> 38:49.462
This is all your fault!
All of it!

38:49.495 --> 38:52.432
( door opens )

38:52.465 --> 38:53.834
Jury's back.

39:05.478 --> 39:07.113
The defendant
will please rise.

39:08.882 --> 39:11.451
Mr. Foreman, the jury
has reached its verdict?

39:11.484 --> 39:12.118
We have.

39:12.152 --> 39:13.887
What say you?

39:13.920 --> 39:18.424
"326447 -- Commonwealth
vs Edward Wicks.

39:18.458 --> 39:20.627
"on the count of murder
in the first degree,

39:20.661 --> 39:23.764
"we find the defendant,
Edward Wicks, not guilty.

39:23.797 --> 39:28.669
"326448 -- on the count
of murder in the second degree,

39:28.702 --> 39:32.639
we find the defendant,
Edward Wicks, not guilty."

39:33.574 --> 39:35.408
What?

39:35.441 --> 39:37.443
Members of the jury,
this completes your service.

39:37.477 --> 39:38.879
You call that service?

39:38.912 --> 39:41.515
What are you, morons?
Ms. Gamble! Ms. Gamble!

39:41.548 --> 39:43.750
What, do you like the color
of Mr. Donnell's tie?

39:43.784 --> 39:46.553
Ms. Gamble!
I don't care, judge!
That's it!

39:46.587 --> 39:48.889
That's it.
This is what happens

39:48.922 --> 39:50.557
when you get 12 people

39:50.591 --> 39:53.527
too stupid to get out
of jury duty.

39:53.560 --> 39:54.961
You end up with a bunch
of unemployed,

39:54.995 --> 39:57.063
brain-dead idiots!

39:57.097 --> 39:58.799
Tell me,
what would it take here?

39:58.832 --> 40:00.934
Did he have to stab the guy
eight times?

40:00.967 --> 40:03.436
One more word!
Come on, raise your hands!

40:03.469 --> 40:06.172
Which one of you retards
voted not guilty?

40:06.206 --> 40:08.141
All right, Helen.
That's it.
You're in contempt.

40:08.174 --> 40:10.511
Throw them in contempt!

40:10.544 --> 40:12.112
Why don't you
invite the defendant over

40:12.145 --> 40:13.680
for Christmas dinner, huh?

40:13.714 --> 40:16.149
Let him carve the turkey,
you idiots!

40:16.182 --> 40:17.017
Get her out!
Take her away!

40:17.050 --> 40:20.787
Not guilty by reason
of jury's insanity!

40:20.821 --> 40:22.488
You morons!

40:22.523 --> 40:25.892
Bailiff, take
Mr. Donnell away, too.

40:25.926 --> 40:27.528
He knows why.

40:27.561 --> 40:28.662
What did you do?

40:28.695 --> 40:30.831
It's a long story.

40:35.201 --> 40:38.539
so, that leaves you and me
to celebrate, right?

40:38.572 --> 40:40.440
Maybe next time.

40:53.887 --> 40:57.891
Well, at least he let us
share the same cell.

41:00.260 --> 41:04.631
Yep. Won't Lindsay
be thrilled,

41:04.665 --> 41:06.767
you and I sharing
a room again?

41:06.800 --> 41:08.969
Funny.

41:09.002 --> 41:12.873
Okay, tell me.
I can take it.

41:12.906 --> 41:15.976
Did I make a mistake
in the trial?

41:16.009 --> 41:18.244
Should I have done
something differently?

41:18.278 --> 41:20.013
What, did I appear
unsympathetic,

41:20.046 --> 41:22.148
returning
with a concussion?

41:22.182 --> 41:23.717
I don't know.

41:23.750 --> 41:26.620
The medical examiner
didn't help you much.

41:53.847 --> 41:55.682
Maybe I could have
handled things better.

41:55.716 --> 41:59.686
It doesn't work. That's why
I'm like I am in there.

41:59.720 --> 42:03.156
The process doesn't work.
I get frustrated.

42:03.189 --> 42:07.694
Well, maybe it could work
if you do things right.

42:07.728 --> 42:10.296
Works worse
when I do things right.

42:10.330 --> 42:14.868
Why don't you
get off the bench?

42:14.901 --> 42:18.772
It's a thought.

42:18.805 --> 42:22.609
French fries?

42:28.849 --> 42:30.951
Two more hours,
you can go.

43:22.035 --> 43:23.103
You stinker!
